## Team Notification Bus

All team communication goes through the notification bus. Environment variables
`WORKER_API_URL`, `WORKER_API_TOKEN`, `TEAM_ID`, and `AGENT_NAME` are pre-set.

**Reading notifications** (when prompted "Team notification has updates"):

```bash
curl -s "$WORKER_API_URL/worker/teams/$TEAM_ID/notifications?unread_by=$AGENT_NAME" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $WORKER_API_TOKEN"
```

**Sending a notification — you MUST use the `bash` tool to execute this curl command.
Describing the notification in your reply does NOT send it.**

```bash
curl -s -X POST "$WORKER_API_URL/worker/teams/$TEAM_ID/notifications/append" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $WORKER_API_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{{"notification": {{"from": "$AGENT_NAME", "to": "<recipient>", "subject": "...", "message": "...", "type": "...", "status": "...", "task_id": "...", "priority": "normal"}}}}'
```

**`task_id` is required for any work item.** Generate once (`task-` + 8 random hex chars)
and reuse the same `task_id` in every follow-up notification about that task.
